{
  "name": "Hinderance: Addicted",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/consumables/drinks/alcohol-jug-spirits-brown.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>An addict is reliant on a particular harmful substance to function, such as alcohol, coffee, or drugs. When you finish a 24 hour period without satiating your addition, you gain a level of exhaustion (maximum of 5) which cannot be removed until you succumb to or suppress your addiction. One of your Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, or Charisma scores of your choice increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p><p>After 21 consecutive days of abstinence, your addiction is suppressed until you imbibe the substance again.</p>",
